kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Validator chains short-circuit on first failure and no-op on empty input — reuse this pattern in src/validation/compose.ts.\",\"scope\":\"src/validation/compose.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Track merged branches via a _mergedBranches Set in the retry-queue; expose skipMerged/unskipMerged/isMerged methods rather than mutating queue items.\",\"scope\":\"src/utils/retry-queue.ts\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T18:15:18.992Z","wordCount":595,"positions":[2,10,18,31,38,51,58,64,78,87,91,94,115,118,127,139,149,161,171,179,191,198,211,218,228,235,241,252,258,270,273,279,285,293,304,315,319,330,338,344,352,356,367,375,382,389,400,407,413,420,429,436,451,462,468,475,482,493,506,515,523,530,535,544,550,559,567,571,577,583,589]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"compose","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"New public APIs (`composeWithSkip`, `skipMerged`) were unit-tested but never wired to any production call site — integration must be verified explicitly.\",\"scope\":\"src/validation/compose.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Unit tests alone are insufficient; a feature needs at least one integration test showing it wired to an actual production code path.\",\"scope\":\"testing\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Extended existing `retry-queue.ts` with `skipMerged`/`isMerged`/`unskipMerged` rather than creating a new module, keeping state co-located with the queue logic.\",\"scope\":\"src/utils/retry-queue.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Branches are identified by target ID; `skipMerged` uses a `Set<string>` keyed on target ID to track which branches have been merged.\",\"scope\":\"compose retry\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T18:18:16.264Z","wordCount":839,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,59,66,73,92,110,115,126,132,141,145,156,161,168,180,188,197,211,219,223,234,242,249,256,265,272,277,283,293,309,317,326,332,336,348,353,364